**Summary:**
The Unity SDK is a plugin that integrates Amplitude's iOS and Android SDKs into Unity projects (2019.3.11+), supporting installation via Unity Package Manager or manual download. It provides event tracking, user property management, revenue tracking, and session handling, but doesn't support pure desktop or Editor environments.

**Keywords:**
- Unity SDK integration
- Android/iOS platform support
- Event tracking
- User properties
- Revenue tracking
- IDFA/COPPA compliance
- EU data residency
- Dynamic configuration
- Session management
- Batch event uploading